				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">You should at least design them, just so there are more sources of materials.  You would sell a few to developers here, but don't expect to sell much more other than for one or two repros that need specific boards.  All other repro makers will still use the much cheaper donor carts.
<br />
<br />I have had MMC3/VRC2/VRC4/etc boards available for homebrew production for a while, but I don't expect them to be used by anyone in the next few years.  They cost me ~$12 with no profit, while an enhanced UNROM is under $3.  Going from a $30 homebrew to $40 would be a large hit to sales so it will need a very good (and actually finished) game to justify the added cost.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

