					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">MottZilla wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">With the 32K CHR-RAM, is it just hooking up the upper bits to hold a 8KB CHR-RAM page I would guess?</div><br />You could still use the regular MMC3 CHR switching scheme (i.e. 4 1KB chunks + 2 2KB chunks), but restricted to those 32KB of CHR-RAM. This would be really useful for character and background animation, pretty much in the same way as CHR-ROM is.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Part of the reason to havea MMC3 for honebrew is definitely to have alot of CHR, which no homebrew yet has needed but certainly could happen. Alot of great games have such nice graphics thanks to tons of CHRROM.</div>
<br />Yeah, giving up CHR-ROM is not such a great idea, since that would certainly exclude the repro folks. For us developers though, the 32KB of CHR-RAM is almost as good, the only advantage being that the graphics will occupy space in the PRG-ROM, which has the fairly low limit of 512KB.</div>

